text: Julianne Moore and Molly Ringwald's Daughters Make Their Modeling Debuts at New York Fashion Week by Jennifer Drysdale 1:59   Julianne Moore and Molly Ringwald's Daughters Make Their Modeling Debuts at New York Fashion Week New York Fashion Week is ushering in a new generation of Hollywood offspring! Julianne Moore and Molly Ringwald's daughters both made their modeling debuts at NYFW on Sunday, starring in a J.Crew presentation. Moore understandably couldn't contain her pride, posting a photo of her 14-year-old daughter, Liv Freundlich, on Instagram. "@Jcrew beauties @lisaeisnerjewelry and my very own @livfreundlich ‚ù§#realpeople," she captioned the pic. A post shared by Julianne Moore (@juliannemoore) on Feb 12, 2017 at 1:48pm PST A post shared by Julianne Moore (@juliannemoore) on Feb 12, 2017 at 2:33pm PST RELATED: Julianne Moore Brings Lookalike Daughter Liv Freundlich to New York Fashion Week -- See the Cute Pics! Ringwald also took to Instagram to express her excitement for her daughter, 13-year-old Mathilda Gianopoulos. "Stage mom üòè #jcrewnyfw #jcrew," she wrote alongside a snap of herself sitting with her daughter backstage, before sharing snaps of Mathilda in action. A post shared by Molly Ringwald (@mollyringwald) on Feb 12, 2017 at 12:32pm PST A post shared by Molly Ringwald (@mollyringwald) on Feb 12, 2017 at 12:27pm PST A post shared by Molly Ringwald (@mollyringwald) on Feb 12, 2017 at 1:56pm PST Ringwald and Moore's daughters aren't the only celeb kids at New York Fashion Week. Kelsey and Camille Grammer's 15-year-old daughter, Mason, walked the runway for Malan Breton last week. See more in the video below. RELATED SLIDESHOW
